25|$|The Tracy Thermal Generating Station {{was one of}} four {{peaking power}} plants on the Hydro-Québec grid. It was {{primarily}} used in winter to boost capacity, as required by the widespread use of <b>electric</b> <b>heating</b> and poor home insulation in Quebec. It was also sporadically operated as a base load power plant between 1989 and 1991, in 1998 and in 2003-2004 to mitigate low water conditions in the company's reservoirs.|$|E
