25|$|Prior to the mid-20th century, bed bugs {{were very}} common. According {{to a report}} by the UK Ministry of Health, in 1933, all the houses in many areas had some degree of bed bug infestation. The {{increase}} in bed bug populations in the early 20th century has been attributed to the advent of <b>electric</b> <b>heating,</b> which allowed bed bugs to thrive year-round instead of only in warm weather.|$|E
